physical_examinations.relevant_findings: 28-year-old woman with multiple painful benign nerve sheath tumors, bilateral retromastoid scalp region masses causing sleep disturbance, local tenderness, and distal neuropathic pain in the distributions of bilateral saphenous nerves, bilateral sciatic nerves, left femoral nerve, and left mons pubis. No stigmata of NF1 or NF2, no dermatological features, and no other clinical features of NF1 or NF2.
